vote. I -- it's
been my policy since I've been
in the United

12:20.206 --> 12:24.510 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
States Senate, and I presided
over more Supreme
Court nominees than anyone in
history, anyone

12:24.544 --> 12:26.446 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
living.

12:26.479 --> 12:31.317 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And never once, even the ones
that I've disagreed
with, have they been denied a
hearing. And

12:31.351 --> 12:37.090 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
so I think the Democrats should
not take up
what I think is a fundamentally
unconstitutional

12:37.123 --> 12:42.028 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
notion that the Republicans --
Republicans
initiated 10 months ago. I think
they should

12:42.061 --> 12:44.964 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
see who they nominate and vote
on them.

12:44.998 --> 12:49.135 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, you've seen
the list
of names that president-elect
Trump has put

12:49.168 --> 12:54.007 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
